The paper deals with signal and image processing in the context of medical ultrasound imaging. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and bioinformatics (cs.BIO). However, given the focus on image processing and artifact removal, cs.CV is the most likely category. The use of component-based modeling and processing also suggests a potential fit with cs.IT and cs.SI. The application to medical imaging suggests a potential fit with cs.BIO, while the use of ultrasound imaging suggests a potential fit with cs.MM.
